Red Sox Trounce Rangers to Lead AL East as Yankees Lose to Athletics in 10

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-08-25T04:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/red-sox-trounce-rangers-to-lead-al-east-as-yankees-lose-to-athletics-in-10.html
The  Boston Red Sox  defeated the
Texas Rangers 13-2 to take over first place in the American
League East ahead of the New York Yankees, who lost 6-4 to the
Oakland Athletics in 10 innings.  The results yesterday leave the Red Sox (79-50) one game
ahead of the Yankees (77-50) in Major League Baseball’s five-
team AL East.  The Red Sox led 7-1 through five innings last night and
made it 13-1 after eight as Jacoby Ellsbury, Carl Crawford and
Adrian Gonzalez hit two-run homers in consecutive innings at
Rangers Ballpark in Arlington, Texas.  At Yankee Stadium, Coco Crisp hit his second home run of
the game in the 10th inning to snap a 3-3 tie and give the
Athletics a 6-3 lead. Nick Swisher hit his second solo home run
in the bottom of the 10th.  Mark Teixeira also had a home run for the Yankees, in the
eighth inning, to tie teammate Curtis Granderson with 35 this
season.  Jose Bautista  of the  Toronto Blue Jays  leads the major
leagues with 37 home runs.  New York ’s Robinson Cano doubled in the fourth inning to
extend his hitting streak to 15 games.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
